race.comment: CHEERFUL CAT (13) needed it first up and then did a good job beaten a head over 1800m here on the turf. Doubt the switch to the turf will be an issue, and he has scope for more improvement. Will finish hard and can get the job done. CHAYSE 'N' LEISA (6) peaks off two wins at the track over the 1550m. He races forward and looks capable of taking the next step. BEST COFFEE (5) was back to his best winning a 60 at the Sunshine Coast over 1400m. First try on synthetic today but is worth following up. BIRMINGHAM (2) turned the form around winning here this grade/trip. He's been freshened and the 3kg claim assists again in the weight department. Has to be considered. FOREVER FORTUNE (8) has a 3kg claim today and won't be far away.
